# Git Commit Message Format

## Structure
```
type(scope): description

[optional body]
[optional footer]
```

## Types
- `feat`: New feature
- `fix`: Bug fix
- `refactor`: Code change that neither fixes nor adds
- `style`: Formatting, styling changes
- `docs`: Documentation only
- `test`: Adding or updating tests
- `chore`: Maintenance tasks

## Scopes
- `game`: Game logic and flow
- `ui`: UI components
- `questions`: Question data/management
- `scores`: Scoring system
- `auth`: Authentication (if added)
- `i18n`: Internationalization

## Examples
```
feat(game): add countdown timer to questions

fix(ui): correct RTL alignment on answer buttons

refactor(questions): extract question fetching to custom hook

style(ui): update button colors to match design system

docs: add setup instructions to README
```

## Guidelines
- Use imperative mood ("add" not "added")
- Keep subject line under 72 characters
- No period at end of subject line
- Reference issues in footer: `Closes #123`
